rComments: Prof. Hagerman is very kind, he is helpful during office hours. However, this course was poorly structured, lectures seemed not to contribute to learning. If you want to learn a lot, don't take this course, but if you like dynamic lectures, go for it.

Not a fan of the course material but Professor Hagerman did his best to make things interesting. I could have used a textbook or a timeline at least, lectures were confusing and jumped about a bit in time period.

Fantastic story-teller, and genuinely a really nice guy. Unfortunately, his lectures are unclear, and there's no textbook, so I had no idea what to study when the exam rolled around. He did give out the exam on the last day of class so we could prepare for it beforehand, though, so it wasn't so bad. He's gives really good feedback on essays, too.

He really cares about his students and is very passionate about his work. 20% of our grade was purely on participation and attendance. He's a tough grader, but he's really funny and manages to make class very interesting. You have to work for your mark!!! Make sure to see him about your essays! He is EXCELLENT with feedback and constructive crit.
